It's time to smash our bedroom. The last room in the house where, apart from a bit of decorating, nothing has been done.
The disgusting electric fireplace and the fireplace floor must go. We must enclose the chimney, replace and smooth out the cracked plaster, and then build a custom-made wardrobe.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch...
The dirty part of the job is done.
At the back of the chimney, we found a few dead birds, very desiccated.
Everything is ready for the plasterer next week.
The small side recess turned out well.
Here comes a new wardrobe in (but we haven't even started on the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look, what we found behind the heater!
And we've even thought of incorporating this nice little ventilation flap, so the chimney doesn't get damp.
The chimney sweep installed the covering and hood. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest up there.
The plasterer is finished. Tomorrow the floor will be laid.
The cork underlayment is in place, I've rigged up a toilet paper roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner.
The floor tiles are finished and can be laid. We're taking a tea break.
Oh dear. Progress is slow today, due to super complicated cuts around the door posts, so we can have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor is also being laid). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me.
Finally, but at last! The crowning glory was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
The hallway floor and all the baseboards are still missing. The decorator is coming in a month, so we have a rough plaster finish for now.
Some additional Heimwerker work in the evening to saw or plane the lower sections around the door posts, where the floor should fit in seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlayment is now also in the hallway.
Yesterday we finished the hallway floor! Then out at 5 am to pick up item 1 from Heathrow, a quick nap and a final push in the hallway, the baseboards are in place. The joints will be filled in once the adhesive is dry.
